----------
Installation of Net::DelCheck
----------
Dependencies:
	Net::DNS::SEC
	Net::DNS::TestNS
	XML::DOM

Present as package in ubuntu: libnet-dns-sec-perl
The rest has to be installed with cpan.

----------
Compilation of the server on ubuntu server 10.04 LTS 
----------
perl Install.PL --verbose --configure --prefix=$HOME/bin/whoisserver --sqluser=root --sqlpass=root --dbname=ripe
connexion as root because the install script want to create the database ripe_'name after --dbname='

Install.PL want javac 'in the PATH', the check looks like that: 
	my $java = `locate javac | grep bin | head -1 | xargs dirname`;
We also have to install openjdk-6-jdk and run updatedb.

Dependencies: 
	openjdk-6-jdk
	libtool
	automake
	libssl-dev
	libglib2.0-dev
	libmysqld-dev
	flex
	bison
	libc-client-dev
	libperl-dev

third party libs: 
	libxslt-dev
	libxml2-dev


./build.sh has to be run by bash, not sh (errors with pushd and popd)
desactivate the compilation of the third party libraries imap-2004, libxslt and libxml : CCCOMP=0, LIBXMLCOMP=0 and LIBXSLTCOMP=0 in build.sh

Changes in Install.PL: 
set debug mode : my $Debug       = 1;
configure --with-rdns --prefix=$DbPrefix --with-erl=$^X --with-rpslvariant=$RPSLVariant --with-cclientinc=$Cwd/third-party/lib-c-client --with-cclientlib=$Cwd/third-party/lib-c-client ] );
(add --with-cclientinc and --with-cclientlib)

make cannot find libxml/tree.h: export C_INCLUDE_PATH=/usr/include/libxml2/

Hardcoded library paths: 
third-party/libxslt_1.1.12-8/lib/libxslt.a: No such file or directory
	mkdir third-party/libxslt_1.1.12-8/lib/ ; cd third-party/libxslt_1.1.12-8/lib/ &&  ln -s /usr/lib/libxslt.a && cd -
third-party/libxml2_2.6.16-7sarge1/lib/libxml2.a: No such file or directory
	mkdir third-party/libxml2_2.6.16-7sarge1/lib/ ; cd third-party/libxml2_2.6.16-7sarge1/lib/ &&  ln -s /usr/lib/libxml2.a && cd -


--------------
Compilation of c-client
--------------

In the c-client directory: 
make lsu SSLTYPE=unix.nopwd 'EXTRACFLAGS=-O2 -mtune=native -pipe -fPIC'

In the server Directory: 
Set lib and src for the server: 
	cd third-party && ln -s /home/raphael/whois/c-client/imap-2007e/c-client/ lib-c-client && cd -


